SUMMARY:Portland Veggie Board Gamers (with Portland Metro Veggies!)
DESCRIPTION:Portland Area Board Games and RPGs\nVeggie board gamers come together to eat\, drink\, play games and make friends. (We also enjoy just chatting.) Come learn new games and meet new people\, every Monday.\n\nFOOD\nThe menu at the Bye and Bye is 100% vegan.\n\nGAMES\nWe tend to play party games and other light games\, but strategy games and other medium-weight games are welcome too. Feel free to bring a game if you have one you want to play! I always bring a variety of games that I'm happy to teach.\nPast plays include games like Codenames\, Forbidden Island\, Ticket to Ride\, Camel Up\, Just One\, Dixit\, Deep Sea Adventure\, Chameleon\, Splendor\, and Azul.\n\nLOGISTICS\nPlease join us any time throughout the evening. Check the comments for possible updates.\nOnce we have a table\, I will leave a comment below and do my best to indicate where we are seated. Look for the pile of board games and the short green sign that says "Veggie Board Games". If you arrive late and can't find us\, send Evan a chat message through Meetup or comment on the page\, and I will do my best to respond\, although sometimes messages are delayed.\n\nPlease keep your RSVP (going/ not going) up to date. This event is also posted under [Portland Metro Veggies](https://www.meetup.com/portland-metro-veggies/) as "Veggie Board Game Night". You can RSVP for either event.\n\nHappy Gaming!
